## [0.6.0] - 2025-11-25

### Summary
AI Terminal - Multi-provider AI chat interface with encrypted storage and automatic fallback. 8 providers integrated (200+ models).

### Added
- **AI Providers (8):**
  - OpenRouter (200+ models, free tier 50 req/day)
  - Groq (fast inference, LPU-powered)
  - HuggingFace (open-source models)
  - Mistral (European AI, GDPR-friendly)
  - Google Gemini (1M token context)
  - OpenAI (GPT-4o, o1)
  - Anthropic (Claude 3.5 Sonnet)
  - xAI (Grok)

- **Security:**
  - AES-256-CBC encrypted API key storage (IndexedDB)
  - Session-based password with expiry (auto-logout after 1 hour)
  - Password-protected access to API keys
  - Keys never logged or transmitted

- **Reliability:**
  - Automatic fallback system (switches providers on error)
  - Graceful error handling (rate limits, invalid keys, network errors)
  - Retry logic with exponential backoff

- **UX:**
  - Streaming support (real-time responses)
  - Usage tracking per provider (token usage, requests)
  - Model selector with filtering (by provider, capability, context)
  - Provider settings UI (manage API keys, test connections)
  - Floating action button (bottom-right, z-40)
  - Sliding panel (from right, smooth animation)

### Changed
- **Bundle Size:** +45KB AI chunk (lazy loaded)

### Technical
- Files: 15 new files (~2,480 lines of code)
- Core: src/services/ai/ (types, providerRouter, 8 providers)
- Components: AITerminal, ModelSelector, ProviderSettings, UsageTracker
- Store: useTerminalStore.ts (NEW)
- Time: 24 hours

